[1] Global polio update - GPEI 17 Jan 2018
Date: Thu 18 Jan 2018
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative [edited]
http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/this-week/


Poliovirus Weekly Update 17-Jan-2018, World Health Organization
---------------------------------------------------------------
New wild poliovirus cases reported this week: 1
Total number of wild poliovirus cases in 2018: 0
Total number of wild poliovirus cases in 2017: 22

New cVDPV cases reported this week: 5
Total number of cVDPV cases in 2018: 0
Total number of cVDPV cases in 2017: 91

Headlines
Summary of newly-reported viruses this week:
Afghanistan:
- 1 new case of wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) reported in Kandahar province.
- 5 new WPV1 positive environmental samples have been reported, 3 collected from Nangarhar province, 1 from Hilmand province, and 1 from Kunar province.
Pakistan:
- 3 new WPV1 positive environmental samples have been reported, 2 collected from Balochistan province, and 1 from Punjab province.
Democratic Republic of the Congo:
- 5 new cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) have been reported in Tanganyika province.

Afghanistan
- 1 new case of wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) was reported this week from Spinboldak district, Kandahar province. Onset of this latest case was [Thu 28 Dec 2017].
- The total number of officially reported WPV1 cases in Afghanistan in 2017 is now 14.
- 5 new WPV1 positive environmental samples were reported this week. 3 samples were collected in Jalalabad district, Nangarhar province, one on [Mon 25 Dec 2017] and 2 on [Tue 26 Dec 2017]. 1 sample was collected in Asadabad district, Kunar province, on [Mon 25 Dec 2017], and 1 sample was collected in Lashkargah district, Hilmand province, on [Wed 6 Dec 2017].

- A vaccination campaign using bOPV is taking place this week, targeting over 5 million children.

Pakistan
- No new cases of wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) were reported in the past week. The most recent case (by date of onset) was reported in Zhob district, Balochistan province, with onset on [Wed 15 Nov 2017].
- The total number of officially reported WPV1 cases in Pakistan in 2017 remains 8.
- 3 new WPV1 positive environmental samples were reported this week. Two were collected in Balochistan province, one in Zhob district on [Mon 18 Dec 2017], and one in Quetta district on [Wed 20 Dec 2017]. One sample was collected from Lahore district, Punjab province, on [Mon 18 Dec 2017].
- A nationwide vaccination campaign using bOPV is currently taking place, vaccinating over 37 million children, and placing particular emphasis on reaching travelling and missed children.

Nigeria
- No new cases of wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) were reported in the past week. The total number of WPV1 cases for 2016 remains 4 and no cases have been reported in 2017. The most recent case (by date of onset) was reported in Monguno Local Government Area, Borno, with onset on [21 Aug 2016].
- Nigeria continues to implement an emergency response to the detected WPV1 strain and circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) strains affecting the country (last detected in 2016).
- The next round of sub-national immunization days are planned for late January [2018].
- Detection of polio cases in Nigeria underscores the risk posed by low-level undetected transmission. As part of the emergency response, subnational surveillance continues to be strengthened.

Lake Chad Basin
- The detection of wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) (Borno state, Nigeria in 2016) and circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) (Borno and Sokoto states in 2016) continue to pose a risk to the neighbouring countries of the Lake Chad basin.
- Emergency outbreak response efforts continue across the Lake Chad basin, together with activities to fill subnational surveillance gaps across the region.
- These activities include efforts to vaccinate children at markets, in internally displaced persons camps, and at international borders.
- Phase 3 of outbreak response is being launched in January 2018, taking into account the recommendations made during the November [2017] Outbreak Response Assessments for the countries and the Technical Advisory Group meeting in December [2017]. The objective is to maintain and improve the multi-national, regional outbreak response across the Lake Chad basin region, in particular improving operations, reach and surveillance among hard-to-reach areas and populations.

Central Africa
- 5 new cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were confirmed this week in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC). All the cases were reported from Tanganyika province. Up to 3 cases were located in Ankoro district with onset dates on [Sat 11 Nov 2017, Sat 18 Nov 2017, and Sat 25 Nov 2017], and 2 cases were located in Manono district, with onset on [Sun 19 Nov 2017 and Mon 20 Nov 2017].
- The total number of officially reported cVDPV2 cases in the DRC in 2017 is now 17.
- Outbreak response continues to take place across the country, including use of monovalent oral polio vaccine type 2 (mOPV2) in line with internationally-agreed outbreak response protocols. Children living in the districts where the latest cases were reported were last targeted with mOPV2 during December [2017] vaccination days.
- Surveillance and immunization activities continue to be strengthened in neighbouring countries.

Middle East
- No new cases of circulating vaccine derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported this week. The most recent case (by date of onset) was reported in Boukamal district, with onset on [Thu 21 Sep 2017].
- The total number of officially reported cVDPV2 cases in Syria in 2017 remains 74.
- The 1st round of the 2nd phase of the outbreak response started this week in Deir Ez-Zor, Raqqah, and Hasakah governorates.
- Vaccination teams have adjusted the timing of daily activities according to the prevailing security situation in the region. Teams are beginning activities at sunrise and are returning empty mOPV2 vials on the morning of the next campaign day, to allow more time for vaccination visits.

Officially reported wild poliovirus cases as of 16 Jan 2018
Total global cases in 2018: 0 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2017)
- Total in endemic countries in 2018: 0 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2017)
- Total in non-endemic countries in 2018: 0 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2017)

